nl: how many types of prescriber profile are new vs growers
sql:
-- Full temporal analysis cannot be performed as no date columns are specified for filtering new vs growers.
SELECT 
    COUNT(DISTINCT [PrescriberId]) AS [TotalPrescriberProfiles],
    CASE 
        WHEN [ProductPriority] = 'New' THEN 'New'
        WHEN [ProductPriority] = 'Grower' THEN 'Grower'
        ELSE 'Other'
    END AS [ProfileType]
FROM 
    [dbo].[Reporting_BI_PrescriberProfile]
GROUP BY 
    CASE 
        WHEN [ProductPriority] = 'New' THEN 'New'
        WHEN [ProductPriority] = 'Grower' THEN 'Grower'
        ELSE 'Other'
    END

nl: how many new vs growers and decliners are there ? chart them
sql:
-- Note: Full temporal analysis cannot be performed as no date columns are specified for tracking new, growers, and decliners over time.

SELECT 
    COUNT(CASE WHEN [TRX(C4 Wk)] > 0 AND [TRX(P4 Wk)] = 0 THEN 1 END) AS New,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN [TRX(C4 Wk)] > 0 AND [TRX(P4 Wk)] > 0 THEN 1 END) AS Growers,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN [TRX(C4 Wk)] = 0 AND [TRX(P4 Wk)] > 0 THEN 1 END) AS Decliners
FROM 
    [dbo].[Reporting_BI_PrescriberOverview]

nl: use ngd table how many new vs growers and decliners are there ? chart them
sql:
-- Note: Full temporal analysis cannot be performed as no date columns are specified for tracking trends over time.
SELECT 
    [NGDType], 
    COUNT(*) AS [Count]
FROM 
    [dbo].[Reporting_BI_NGD]
GROUP BY 
    [NGDType]
ORDER BY 
    [Count] DESC
